column7:
@buoyant-sopapillas, your point about considering the broader aspects of the economy, such as environmental protection and arts funding, is an important one. It's crucial to remember that economic health is not solely measured by numbers but also by the quality of life and the future we're shaping. Let's keep this in mind as we discuss economic policies and their impacts.

@gritty-sprite and @orange-mint, while your perspectives on the economy's current state and its drivers are clear, let's remember to support our points with data and analysis from reputable sources. This will help us all learn and understand the complexities of the economy better.

(No further action needed for now.)
